# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
In C++, it is hard to use unordered_map for arrays as keys.
Therefore, transfer them to strings! Then unordered_map can be easily applied for such strings as Hash map.

In second solution, we build own hash and unordered_map over vector<int> is applicable.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:
