# Approach I
The bruteforce method would be to compare each row with each column taking $$ O(n^3) $$ time and constant space.


# Approach II
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
By using map (for using vector directly) or unordered map (by converting vector to string) to map every row, and then comparing every column with it.
It takes $$ O(n^2) $$ time and $$ O(n^2) $$ space 

Conversion to string takes extra time and memory, so its better you make your own hash function and use it with <unordered_map> (you can't use vector with unordered map)

